just a question to clarify. are we directly maintaining this pot as master source? i‚Äôm okay, it's simple."}, {'account_id': 10497, 'date': '2015-11-11 13:08:57.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Let me update the commit message... To keep track all our work, I wrote a blueprint.'}, {'account_id': 10497, 'date': '2015-11-11 13:12:22.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-11-11 13:14:30.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+1

Build succeeded (check pipeline).

- gate-i18n-docs http://docs-draft.openstack.org/31/244031/2/check/gate-i18n-docs/336e7b3//doc/build/html/ : SUCCESS in 30s'}, {'account_id': 6547, 'date': '2015-11-11 15:23:18.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

This change should be developed together with how we sync translations in infra for other projects.

As such, I propose to place all files in "i18n/locale" like we do for all other projects - "$repository/locale" is always the path.
And then use language directories. But adding the files *here* is not needed, just import in Zanata and let's download and sync with the usual scripts.

Instead of extracting strings, we could then just make the extracting step a noop - so it would do nothing ;)

What do you think?'}, {'account_id': 10497, 'date': '2015-11-12 00:08:56.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

I agree to the suggestion from Andreas.

"i18n/locale" looks a little strange, but sounds very reasonable to me. We won't to create a own tool as possible, so it is a great idea to use the existing infra tool chains.'}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2015-11-12 03:25:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

I agree with Andreas that we should follow the same directory structure.

Regarding the directory name, how about "terminology/locale".
We are also planning to support translations for our document.
Once it is supported, we will have multiple "locale" directory.'}, {'account_id': 6547, 'date': '2015-11-12 06:01:02.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Akihiro-san, it's really $repository/locale - and the repo is called i18n. Sure, this can be done differently in the infra scripts but is an extra step.

If you plan to add more than one locale dir, using a different name is needed but the simplest way to use the infra scripts is i18n/locale. I suggest you stick with one dir for now, adjust the infra scripts - and then came back here renaming if needed."}, {'account_id': 3108, 'date': '2015-11-12 07:19:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

I think i18n-term is a better folder name. The ideal solution is to have two locale folders: i18n-term/locale and doc/locale.
But I understand the easiest way is to use i18n/locale.
Could we create a different script as horizon project which has two locale folders? Is it hard to maintain ?'}, {'account_id': 10497, 'date': '2015-11-12 07:38:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

If we are discussing about "doc/" translation, I think doc translation is another topic across all development project. I think we can create another common infra job for "doc/source" as publish-doc job.'}, {'account_id': 3108, 'date': '2015-11-12 08:44:52.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 3108, 'date': '2015-11-12 08:47:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

I reorganized the structure as Andreas suggested.
The translation of "doc" will be taken into consideration with other projects together, as suggested by KATO.'}, {'account_id': 10497, 'date': '2015-11-12 08:48:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

$LANG/LC_MESSAGES should be under "locale".

For example, "i18n/ja/LC_MESSAGES/term.po" should be "i18n/locale/ja/LC_MESSAGES/term.po".'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-11-12 08:50:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified+1

Build succeeded (check pipeline).

- gate-i18n-docs http://docs-draft.openstack.org/31/244031/3/check/gate-i18n-docs/63d65bb//doc/build/html/ : SUCCESS in 25s'}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2015-11-12 09:07:30.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

Isn't the expected path <project>/locale/<lang>/LC_MESSAGES/<project>.po?

commit_message:
Only take the first global, non temporary ipv6 address

Taking a temporary IPv6 address created through the OS' support for
Privacy Extensions (RFC 4941) is not very useful. It would occur because
it happened to be the first in the list returned from ip(8). Instead,
grab the first IPv6 address that is not a temporary address.

Related-Bug: #1488691

Change-Id: I7f455572241e7d0c7406f173239a2270a4d8926a

commit_message:
Fix AttributeError in multinode jobs

I62006b7e636b1773f4f41709cfec1fd6daae3c4f introduced a bug where
the `skip_checks` method tries to access a compute client but the
compute client is not yet setup because the `setup_clients` has
not been called yet (`skip_checks` is always called before  `setup_clients`)
Hence the AttributeError.

The fix gets the number of compute nodes available through a newly introduced
config flag [1]. This way we don't dynamically discover the number of compute
nodes and we don't have to call any client.

[1]: I7d7230d100901179a1d1a0281aa8be990d00c02a

Closes-Bug: #1516561
Change-Id: I1b9474d2f0f0c2edea5ade4381c4c079804f10d5

commit_message:
add initiator to v2 calls for additional auditing

currently notifications are emitted for v2 calls, but the
initiator field is not filled in.

Co-authored-by: sam leong <chio-fai-sam.leong@hpe.com>

Change-Id: Ie2c3fe8d105d59ab89b7f6625e159d4eb6e923b0
Closes-Bug: #1485035
(cherry picked from commit 84b2285a1e1e52213f629d1c54a86eb7565142e4)

commit_message:
Rename references to compute floating IPs client

The single network client is being split out into multiple
clients, one of which will be called FloatingIpsClient. This patch
renames references to the compute floating ips client (floating_ips_client
changed to compute_floating_ips_client) to avoid confusion or conflicts
with the new neutron floating IPs client in code that will reference both
the nova and neutron floating IPs clients.

Partially implements blueprint consistent-service-method-names

Change-Id: Ie6dbd6d490a12bd8c62abbf73e1e848cc35f7d64

commit_message:
Resolve nested get_file in nested yaml/template.

For now, heatclient only resolve nested template if this
template contains heat template header. This patch extend
this function to all yaml/json files.

Change-Id: I619cecf16fc8ca3b1dbef54283b42b9b81f3b103

commit_message:
Support initialization state in Backup Manager

This commit adds is_working method to Backup Manager class to
return initialization state of the underlying volume drivers and
indicate that service has some problems and isn't running correctly.
This is used to block refreshing Service heartbeats if Manager will
return False from is_working.

Related-Bug: 1446750
Change-Id: I3165d01f60bd80ead5163d8678886bd2828af3f9

commit_message:
Rename get_server_group to show_server_group

[GET /resources] methods should be "list_<resource name>s"
or "show_<resource name>", so this patch applies the rule
to server_group client.

Partially implements blueprint consistent-service-method-names

Change-Id: I75307176c2f032301da6227249070c42af54dd6e
